**Root cause:** Every test follows the same template — call the method, maybe `Assert.IsNotNull`, done. This is the classic "coverage-touching" anti-pattern: the coverage tool sees every line executed, but no test actually checks the *outcome*. You get 95% coverage with effectively 0% verification.
